primary_host.about: I'm a native New Yorker and an Airbnb Super host. I have traveled to over 34 countries and understand what it's like on both sides .. as a guest and as a host. I'm a creative professional , play guitar and perform with my band...

sectioned_description.access:
l do prefer to greet guests upon arrival and show them how everything works since this is a shared apartment. l also will provide check in after 8PM with a lock box outside the building so if you do have a late flight please make sure to let me know. Please keep in communication with me if there any changes to your travel plans that l should be aware of. 

Also, l am very flexible when there are issues with travel that are beyond the control of guests like weather or flight delays. Please make sure you are able to email using airbnb messaging system on day of arrival just in case there is a problem. l do allow guests to leave bags on check out day if you have a very late flight and want to explore the city one more time.
sectioned_description.description:
Private Room W. 80's Manhattan 2 blocks from Subway  3 blocks walk to Central Park. Full Size Futon Bed for 2 , Wifi, access to kitchen and shared bathroom. Best Neighborhood in NYC to stay! Very Safe! This top Floor walk up apartment is very quiet for sleeping, !

This room is in a pre war apartment building in the heart of the upper West Side of Manhattan.  It's on the top floor with 4 flights to walk up but l will always help guests with luggage. The room is small but is very comfortable with 2 large windows and lot's of sunlight in the afternoon hours and dark in the morning. lt's also very quiet as the room faces the back of the building and the apartment is on the top floor so there's little to no noise from above. 

The bed is a Futon style Full Size Bed . My guests have said it's very comfortable . l maintain the utmost privacy for guests when l home. l have ceiling to wall curtains  that are set up to add more privacy for when there is another person staying in the apartment 

 Wifi hi speed internet, Large  Flat  Screen TV and DVD player plus Directv Satellite service. There is an eat in kitchen with table. The bathroom is adjacent to the kitchen. The kitchen has a table for eating or using your computer. 

Your room faces  the back of the apartment. There are three rooms total and my room is separated from the guests room by the middle room.  We call this a "Railroad Style" apartment.

l provide baggage service within reason. Leave your bags the day you check out and pick them up later.

l do prefer to greet guests upon arrival and show them how everything works since this is a shared apartment. l also will provide check in after 8PM with a lock box outside the building so if you do have a late flight please make sure to let me know. Please keep in communication with me if there any changes to your travel plans that l should be aware of. 

Also, l am very flexible when there are issues with travel that are beyond the control of guests like weather or flight delays. Please make sure you are able to email using airbnb messaging system on day of arrival just in case there is a problem. l do allow guests to leave bags on check out day if you have a very late flight and want to explore the city one more time.

l am very interactive with my guests if they choose to avail themselves of my experience as a native New Yorker. l know many of the best places to eat and drink and have fun in NYC. This is one of the many advantages of staying here as others have noted in their reviews. l really try to give my guests the best best experience possible while respecting their privacy.

.

Upper West Side UWS W 80's is the best, safest and prettiest neighborhood in NYC. Central Park is just 2 avenue blocks away. Museum of Natural History is 10 blocks walk. There are dozens of quaint outdoor cafes and many inexpensive places to to eat with a wide variety of ethnic food. 

Cross Town bus across the park to the Met Museum on 5th Avenue 85 th street. Also the Guggenheim. Lincoln Center and Columbus Circle are within 10 minutes walk.  10 min. from Times Square and 20 from the 9/11 museum. The famous celebrity Westsider's shop at Fairway, Trader's Joe's and Zabars.  

We have the most beautiful sunsets on the Hudson River, eat or drink at the Boat Basin in Riverside Park at 79th street. Bike riding on the city's bike paths and hudson river and citibike rentals allover Manhattan.

Subway #1,2,3 and B,C  Buses M84, M5, M7, M104 and M11. Columbus Ave Bike lanes and citibike rental spots

l provide baggage service within reason. Leave your bags the day you check out and pick them up later.

 l should note that the apartment is old and if you are used to a more "modern" experience then this may not be best for you. lf you are looking for clean, comfortable, convenient and safe with a Super Host then this place is for you. Please look at pictures and ask for additional pictures if you are not sure. l charge a one time $5 cleaning fee which is for the laundry for clean sheets towels etc. regardless of how long the visit is.

sorted_reviews.comments: Mark is a fantastic, friendly and welcoming host! I thoroughly enjoyed staying in his apartment. The apartment is at a prime location with access to easy transportation, great venues around, and all in all a great place to be at. The apartment was very clean and quiet! I would definitely recommend you stay with Mark!!! 5 stars!

Mark was so amazing. He was very accommodating with us as we were trying to pack a weeks visit into two days. Mark also gave us so many helpful hints, directions, things to do and see and was very good and checking in a communicating with us while we were out and about. Thank you Mark!!

Mark’s place is ideal if you want to spend your day out in the city. It’s in a great location, very safe, and with plenty of privacy. It’s no luxury hotel, but Mark is transparent about that.  He was very easy to communicate with throughout our stay, and very hospitable. I recommend his place if you are mostly looking for a place to sleep and leave your bags while you’re out.

I was so happy to find refuge at Mark's place. He is low-key, generous with his time. Checking in was easy, he made himself available to me when I left, allowed me to leave my bags for a few hours. Love the neighborhood, Zabar's is a few blocks away, the subway, too. Climbing up to the fifth floor is a bit of a challenge, but do-able. Quiet space, privacy in spite of sleeping opposite the front door. I felt very welcome here.

Mark’s apartment is really cute and in a great neighborhood . You truly get to experience the real New York City! Mark is an excellent host! A really interesting person! Thank you Mark! See you in Greece soon!
Marks place is amazing! Super convenient, 2 parking garages on his street, one directly next door. Super clean, marks so friendly and welcoming! Gave us plenty of privacy and made us feel at home
Mark is a great host.  Great location - quiet and convenient.
